parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the IMS (Intermediate Shaft Bearing) can cause the engine to seize, resulting in costly repairs and potential safety risks due to sudden loss of power.
symptoms: Engine seizure
loud noises
and sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature failure of the timing chain can cause engine stalling, loud noises, and catastrophic engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potential safety risks.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loud ticking or snapping sounds
check engine light flashing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the camshaft can cause engine failure, leading to costly repairs and potential safety risks due to sudden loss of power.
symptoms: Engine failure
loud noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Leakage into Cabin and Control Unit Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leakage into the cabin and control unit can cause the vehicle to become inoperable, posing a severe safety risk, especially when driving. This can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden loss of vehicle operation
water flooding into the interior compartment
fungus and mold growth
and the need for costly repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the power window lift mechanic can cause inconvenience and discomfort to the driver and passengers, and may lead to costly repairs not covered under warranty.
symptoms: Power window malfunction
inability to operate the power window
and unexpected repair costs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch cables can cause the vehicle to lose the ability to shift gears, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature clutch failure can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose the ability to shift gears, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents. It can also cause a burning cloud of smoke, which can obstruct the driver's visibility and cause a hazardous situation.
symptoms: The clutch makes a terrible noise
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
a burning cloud of smoke appears.
